original: Björkman, Stig Evald Klasson, praktiserande läkare, Göteborg, f. 5/6/00 i Gbg av med. lic. Klas B. o. Ida Dorotea Janzon. G. 31 m. Ingrid Mattsson. — Stud:ex. i Gbg 20, med. kand. i Upps. 25, med. lic. där 30. E. il’äk. v. Sätra btrunin isiomT. 25 o. 26, dito v. Helsjöns badanst. somm. 30, läk. där 31, 32 o. 34, prakt. läk. i Gbg sed. 30.
translated: Björkman, Stig Evald Klasson was a practicing doctor in Göteborg. He was born on June 5th, 1900 in Göteborg to Klas B. who was a medical graduate and Ida Dorotea Janzon. He got married in 1931 to Ingrid Mattsson and had been a student in Göteborg from 1920 where he passed his exams. He completed his medical degree in Uppsala in 1925 and became a licensed doctor there in 1930. He practiced medicine in Sätra in 1925 and 1926, and also at Helsjöns badanst during summer in 1930. He was a doctor there in 1931, 1932, and 1934. From 1930, he worked as a practicing doctor in Göteborg.
